               <p>JEREMIAH CRAWLEY. I am a <rs id="t18290115-221-viclabel1186" type="occupation">labourer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290115-221-victim1744 t18290115-221-viclabel1186"></join>. I left a coat at my lodging on Monday last; I went down to Greenwich, was sent for on Thursday, and the coat was gone- this is it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290115-221-person1745">
                  MARGARET 
                  DELAY
               <interp inst="t18290115-221-person1745" type="surname" value="DELAY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-221-person1745" type="given" value="MARGARET"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-221-person1745" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prosecutor slept at our house, in <placeName id="t18290115-221-crimeloc1187">Brown Bear-alley</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18290115-221-crimeloc1187" type="placeName" value="Brown Bear-alley"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18290115-221-crimeloc1187" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290115-221-off1184 t18290115-221-crimeloc1187"></join>, on Sunday night, and went to Greenwich on Monday. The prisoner slept there two nights, and on Wednesday he went out with Crawley's coat on; I went up stairs, and the coat was gone - I came down, and opened the street door; he was a good way down the court - I called him, and he came back; I said he had got the young man's coat on - he said he had not; I said he had, and sent for the officer, but before the officer came he pulled it off.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290115-221-person1746">
                  THOMAS 
                  HAYLOCK
               <interp inst="t18290115-221-person1746" type="surname" value="HAYLOCK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-221-person1746" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-221-person1746" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The witness sent for me. I took the prisoner; I asked him how he came to steal it - he said he thought the devil was in him for the moment, but if I would let him go he would enlist for a soldier.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was in liquor.</p>
               <p>THOMAS HAYLOCK. He was not in liquor; the girl who detected him said he had it under his own jacket, and the tail of it tucked up.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18290115-221-verdict1188" type="verdictDescription">
